 ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]'' and [[Adriana Cramer]] on ''[[One Life to Live]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nFumero was born Melissa Gallo in [[North Bergen, New Jersey]], on August 19, 1982.<ref name=\"Fumero\">''[[Soap Opera Digest]]'', Vol. 33, No. 1, January 1, 2008, page 5. \"Gallo will now go by Melissa Fumero\" following her December 9, 2007 marriage to ''OLTL'' costar David Fumero.</ref> She is the daughter of Cuban parents who had moved to the U.S. as teenagers. She grew up in [[Guttenberg, New Jersey]] until she moved to [[Lyndhurst, New Jersey]] aged 6. At 19, she moved to [[New York City]] after getting accepted into [[New York University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/melissafumero/status/1109667465389195265|title=Early life|website=Twitter|first=Melissa|last=Fumero|date=March 23, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2019}}</ref> She received a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts]] in Drama from NYU in 2003.<ref name=\"SOD stats\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/soapstarstats/melissafumerobio |title=Soap Star Stats: Melissa Fumero (Adriana, ''OLTL'') |publisher=SoapOperaDigest.com |accessdate=January 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112225137/http://www.soapoperadigest.com/soapstarstats/melissafumerobio |archivedate=January 12, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nThe second actress to portray Adriana on ''[[One Life to Live]]'', Fumero joined the series on January 20, 2004. Adriana is the long-lost daughter of longtime character [[Dorian Cramer Lord]], portrayed on-and-off since 1979 by [[Daytime Emmy Award|Daytime Emmy]] winner [[Robin Strasser]]. Fumero won the role of Adriana on her last day as a student at NYU.<ref name=\"latintimes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.latintimes.com/melissa-fumero-talks-brooklyn-nine-nine-amy-jake-romance-and-season-2-205769|title=Melissa Fumero Talks 'Brooklyn Nine-Nine' |last=Baral|first=Susmita|date=September 9, 2014|publisher=[[latintimes.com]]|accessdate=May 15, 2018}}</ref> In late 2007 she decided not to renew her contract with the series, but remained on a recurring status to wrap up Adriana's storyline that concluded June 11, 2008. Fumero returned to ''One Life to Live'' in September 2008 for a 15-episode run.<ref name=\"Soaps.com 2008-09\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soaps.com/onelifetolive/news/2247/Melissa_Fumero_Confirms_Her_OLTL_Return_To_Soapsco|title=Melissa Fumero Confirms Her ''OLTL'' Return To Soaps.com!|last=Mistretta|first=Amy|date=September 16, 2008|publisher=[[Soaps.com]]|accessdate=May 12, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081201205233/http://www.soaps.com/onelifetolive/news/2247/Melissa_Fumero_Confirms_Her_OLTL_Return_To_Soapsco|archive-date=December 1, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> Fumero did a guest stint on ''OLTL'' on February 12, 2010, to help usher in the return of [[Kelly Cramer]] ([[Gina Tognoni]]).\n\nFumero made her big-screen debut as the lead in the 2009 independent film ''Tiny Dancer''. In 2010, she appeared in five episodes of [[The CW]]'s ''[[Gossip Girl]]'' as Zoe, one of [[Blair Waldorf]]'s minions. In 2013, she was cast in [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]/[[NBC]]'s ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]'' as [[Amy Santiago]], the female lead opposite [[Andy Samberg]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2013/02/melissa-fumero-to-star-in-foxs-mike-schur-dan-goor-pilot-adam-goldberg-casts-young-self-in-abc-pilot-422727/|title=Melissa Fumero To Star In Fox\u2019s Mike Schur/ Dan Goor Pilot, Adam Goldberg Casts Young Self In ABC Pilot |last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=February 6, 2013|newspaper=Deadline|access-date=February 18, 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref> Fumero made her directorial debut in 2019 when she directed the season 6 episode of ''Brooklyn Nine-Nine'' \"Return of the King\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/RickPage_/status/1088968975625609217|title=Prepping for an exciting week...|last=Page|first=Rick |date=January 25, 2018|website=Twitter|access-date=April 19, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nFumero married her ''[[One Life to Live]]'' co-star [[David Fumero]] on December 9, 2007, and has been credited as Melissa Fumero since.<ref name=\"Fumero\"/><ref name=\"SOD stats\"/> On November 16, 2015, she announced that she was expecting her first child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://instagram.com/p/-J-I79HlLn/|title=Amazing time at our surprise baby shower yesterday. Oh, PS- I'm pregnant. \ud83d\ude1c\ud83d\udc95\ud83d\udc95|website=Instagram}}</ref> On March 24, 2016, she gave birth to a son.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-melissa-fumero-baby-boy-brooklyn-99-20160325-\u2013story.html|title=Melissa Fumero of 'Brooklyn 99' welcomes a baby boy with David Fumero|last=Saad|first=Nardine|website=latimes.com|access-date=February 18, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BDcS9C_HlKV/|title=Sweetest face I've ever held. Enzo 3/24|website=Instagram|first=Melissa|last=Fumero|date=March 26, 2016 |accessdate=February 3, 2019}}</ref> On November 16, 2019, exactly four years after her first announcement, she posted that she was expecting her second child.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B48wH8aBHEr/|title=Melissa Fumero on Instagram: \u201cOh yeah, I\u2019m hella pregnant. To be honest, I haven\u2019t felt like posting about it because this pregnancy has been way harder and... I don\u2019t feel that cute?\u2026\u201d|last=|first=|date=|website=Instagram|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 17, 2019}}</ref> On February 14, 2020, she gave birth to a second son.<ref>https://twitter.com/melissafumero/status/1228782225618919424</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Descent (2007 film)|Descent]]''\n| Dorm Girl #2\n| Uncredited<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dannypeary.blogspot.com/2013/07/on-set-of-tiny-dancer-with-melissa-gallo.html|title=Descent|webs