{"title_page": "Stefan Meissner", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Stefan Meissner\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Stefan Meissner\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1973|3|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Bad Harzburg]], [[West Germany]]\n| height = 1.81 m\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20131989\n| youthclubs1 = FG 16 Vienenburg\n| youthyears2 = 1989\u20131990\n| youthclubs2 = [[Eintracht Braunschweig]]\n| years1 = 1990\u20131994\n| clubs1 = [[Eintracht Braunschweig]]\n| caps1 = 46\n| goals1 = 14\n| years2 = 1994\u20131998\n| clubs2 = [[VfL Wolfsburg]]\n| caps2 = 114\n| goals2 = 19\n| years3 = 1998\u20132000\n| clubs3 = [[Karlsruher SC]]\n| caps3 = 57\n| goals3 = 11\n| years4 = 2000\u20132001\n| clubs4 = [[Stuttgarter Kickers]]\n| caps4 = 18\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2001\u20132004\n| clubs5 = [[Chemnitzer FC]]\n| caps5 = 97\n| goals5 = 19\n| years6 = 2005\u20132006\n| clubs6 = [[VfL Wolfsburg II]]\n| caps6 = 17\n| goals6 = 5\n| totalcaps = 349\n| totalgoals = 68\n| nationalyears1 = 1994\u20131995\n| nationalteam1 = [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2010\u2013\n| managerclubs1 = [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] (youth) \n}}\n\n'''Stefan Meissner''' (born 8 March 1973) is a German former professional [[Association football|football]] who played as a [[forward (association football)|forward]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/2005-06/vfl-wolfsburg-24/1290/spieler_stefan-meissner.html | title = Meissner, Stefan | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref> He spent one season in the [[Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] with [[VfL Wolfsburg]], as well as eight seasons in the [[2. Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga]] with [[Eintracht Braunschweig]], Wolfsburg, [[Karlsruher SC]], and [[Stuttgarter Kickers]]. Meissner had to retire from the game in 2006 due to a [[cartilage]] injury in his knee<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kickersarchiv.de/pmwiki.php/Main/MeissnerStefan | title = Stefan \"Fritze\" Meissner | language = German | publisher = kickersarchiv.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref> and currently works as a youth coach at [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fck.de/de/aktuell/news/details/article/7225-neuer-u17-trainer-beim-fck.html | title = Stefan Mei\u00dfner neuer U17-Trainer beim FCK | language = German | publisher = fck.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n* [[DFB-Pokal]]: runner-up [[1994\u201395 DFB-Pokal|1994\u201395]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Fussballdaten|meissnerstefan|Stefan Meissner}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meissner, Stefan}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Goslar (district)]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Lower Saxony]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:German football managers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Eintracht Braunschweig players]]\n[[Category:VfL Wolfsburg players]]\n[[Category:VfL Wolfsburg II players]]\n[[Category:Karlsruher SC players]]\n[[Category:Stuttgarter Kickers players]]\n[[Category:Chemnitzer FC players]]\n\n\n{{Germany-footy-forward-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Stefan Meissner\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Stefan Meissner\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1973|3|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Bad Harzburg]], [[West Germany]]\n| height = {{Height|m=1.81}}\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20131989\n| youthclubs1 = FG 16 Vienenburg\n| youthyears2 = 1989\u20131990\n| youthclubs2 = [[Eintracht Braunschweig]]\n| years1 = 1990\u20131994\n| clubs1 = [[Eintracht Braunschweig]]\n| caps1 = 46 | goals1 = 14\n| years2 = 1994\u20131998\n| clubs2 = [[VfL Wolfsburg]]\n| caps2 = 114 | goals2 = 19\n| years3 = 1998\u20132000\n| clubs3 = [[Karlsruher SC]]\n| caps3 = 57 | goals3 = 11\n| years4 = 2000\u20132001\n| clubs4 = [[Stuttgarter Kickers]]\n| caps4 = 18 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2001\u20132004\n| clubs5 = [[Chemnitzer FC]]\n| caps5 = 97 | goals5 = 19\n| years6 = 2005\u20132006\n| clubs6 = [[VfL Wolfsburg II]]\n| caps6 = 17 | goals6 = 5\n| nationalyears1= 1994\u20131995\n| nationalteam1= [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany U21]]\n| nationalcaps1= 2 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2010\u2013\n| managerclubs1 = [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] (youth) \n| pcupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Stefan Meissner''' (born 8 March 1973) is a former [[Germany|German]] [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/2005-06/vfl-wolfsburg-24/1290/spieler_stefan-meissner.html | title = Meissner, Stefan | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref> He spent one season in the [[Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] with [[VfL Wolfsburg]], as well as eight seasons in the [[2. Fu\u00dfball-Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga]] with [[Eintracht Braunschweig]], Wolfsburg, [[Karlsruher SC]], and [[Stuttgarter Kickers]]. Meissner had to retire from the game in 2006 due to a [[cartilage]] injury in his knee<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kickersarchiv.de/pmwiki.php/Main/MeissnerStefan | title = Stefan \"Fritze\" Meissner | language = German | publisher = kickersarchiv.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref> and currently works as a youth coach at [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fck.de/de/aktuell/news/details/article/7225-neuer-u17-trainer-beim-fck.html | title = Stefan Mei\u00dfner neuer U17-Trainer beim FCK | language = German | publisher = fck.de | accessdate = 15 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n* [[DFB-Pokal]]: runner-up [[1994\u201395 DFB-Pokal|1994\u201395]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Fussballdaten|meissnerstefan|Stefan Meissner}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Meissner, Stefan}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Goslar (district)]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Lower Saxony]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:German football managers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Eintracht Braunschweig players]]\n[[Category:VfL Wolfsburg players]]\n[[Category:VfL Wolfsburg II players]]\n[[Category:Karlsruher SC players]]\n[[Category:Stuttgarter Kickers players]]\n[[Category:Chemnitzer FC players]]\n\n\n{{Germany-footy-forward-1970s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Add totalcaps and totalgoals. Minor corrections.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stefan_Meissner"}
